<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="view/macro:page/onecolumn"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>

<body>


<div metal:fill-slot="main">
  <h1>Purchase Project Subscription</h1>
  <div class="error message" id="free-hosting-error"
       tal:condition="context/qualifies_for_free_hosting">
    This project does not require a commercial subscription to be purchased.
  </div>
  <div class="error message" id="permission-error"
       tal:condition="not: context/required:launchpad.Admin">
    You do not have permission to purchase a subscription for this project.
  </div>
  <div tal:condition="view/can_purchase_subscription">
    <p>
      This project's licensing does not qualify for free hosting; therefore,
      a subscription needs to be purchased to continue hosting this project on
      Launchpad.
    </p>
    <div>
      Here are the steps to obtain a commercial subscription:
      <ol>
        <li>Purchase a Launchpad subscription in the
          <a tal:define="config modules/canonical.config/config"
             tal:attributes="href config/commercial/purchase_subscription_url">
          Canonical Shop</a>.
        </li>
        <li>You will receive an email that your order has been processed.</li>
        <li>You can then apply the purchased subscription to this project
            on your <a href="/people/+me/+vouchers">
            voucher management page</a>.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    Please review our <a href="/legal">Terms of Use</a>.
  </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
